Ord. No. 20230831-104, Pt. 2, effective September 11, 2023, repealed ยง 25-1-811, which pertained to map;
filing dates and derived from Ord. No. 20080306-073; Ord. No. 20091217-053.

### ARTICLE 17. - INTERLOCAL DEVELOPMENT AGREEMENTS.

In this article:

(1)

DIRECTOR means the Director of the Planning and Development Review Department.

(2)

INTERLOCAL DEVELOPMENT AGREEMENT means an agreement between the City and any governmental
entity, municipal corporation or political subdivision that establishes or modifies
regulations for the use, development, or construction of property containing one or
more existing or proposed structures. The term includes new agreements and amendments
to existing agreements, but does not include agreements or amendments related to roads
or road facilities or the provision of utility services.

Source: Ord. 20091105-068.
